    All Classes and Interfaces

    Class
    Description
    Applicant
    Represents an applicant user in the BTO system.
    ApplicantBoundary
    The ApplicantBoundary class handles the user interface for applicants interacting with the BTO Management System.
    ApplicantControl
    Control class that contains all the business logic for Applicantâ€‘related actions.
    ApplicantRepo
    Repository class that manages all Applicant objects.
    BTOApplication
    Represents an application submitted by an applicant for a BTO project.
    BTOProject
    Represents a Build-To-Order (BTO) housing project with properties like flat types, application period, assigned manager, and officer registrations.
    BTOProjectRepo
    Repository class that manages BTO projects in the system.
    Enquiry
    Represents an enquiry submitted by an applicant regarding a specific BTO project.
    FlatBooking
    Represents a flat booking associated with a BTO application.
    HDBManager
    Represents an HDB Manager user in the system.
    HDBManagerBoundary
    The HDBManagerBoundary class provides the user interface for HDB managers.
    HDBManagerControl
    Control class that handles all business logic related to HDB Manager actions.
    HDBManagerRepo
    Repository class for managing HDBManager users.
    HDBOfficer
    Represents an HDB Officer who is both an applicant and a project handler.
    HDBOfficerBoundary
    The HDBOfficerBoundary class handles the user interface for HDB officers.
    HDBOfficerControl
    Control class for handling all business logic specific to HDB Officers.
    HDBOfficerRepo
    Repository class that manages HDBOfficer accounts.
    IRepo
    An interface representing a generic repository that supports saving to and loading from a CSV file.
    IUserRepo<T>
    An interface for user repositories that manage user objects.
    LoginBoundary
    The LoginBoundary class provides the user interface for login operations.
    LoginControl
    Control class that handles user authentication and post-login routing based on user role (Applicant, HDBOfficer, or HDBManager).
    MainApp
    Entry point of the BTO Management System application.
    OfficerRegistration
    Represents a registration made by an HDB officer to manage a BTO project.
    PasswordChanger
    A utility class that provides functionality to update a user's password.
    Report
    Represents a report generated by an HDB manager summarizing flat bookings.
    User
    Represents a generic user in the system.
    UserMaker
    A utility class to create User objects based on console input.
